title: Star Wars Prologue (2009) - deLimited Productions Fanedit [DVD-9
description:
Summary: This "Prologue" fanedit presents significant plot and character changes to the original Star Wars prequel trilogy. The result is a radically new prequel adventure movie that can be used to better enjoy Episodes IV and V.

For more information about this work, visit the official project page: <a href="
http://digital-fanedits.com/database/faneditor/antimatter/85-star-wars-prologue" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://digital-fanedits.com/database/faneditor/antimatter/85-star-wars-prologue</a>


----------------------------------------------
    Star Wars Prologue (2009) - NTSC DVD9
----------------------------------------------

Premiere released: 19 June, 2009
Revision released: 30 October, 2009
DVD re-release: 1 July, 2011

This high-quality DVD presentation features a
full menu navigation system, English subtitles,
trailers and extra content--including a text
commentary by the faneditor. The disc also
provides a hidden "Acts" menu that can be used
to navigate to each of the movie's four acts.

Video: NTSC (enhanced for 16:9 displays)
Audio: Dolby AC3 5.1 Surround (448kbps)

INSTRUCTIONS. Use the free ImgBurn software to
open the '.mds' file directly. ImgBurn can then
be used to write the dual-layer image correctly
to a blank, DVD-9 disc (Verbatim recommended).
